result.execSummary:
The defendant Kendall Ramone Travis was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Assessments, Repeater], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Kendall Ramone Travis in court with attorney Alexis B Stewart.  Sarra Mae Kiaie appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deputy Court Clerk: rmm.  
JUDGE BOROWSKI FOR JUDGE DALLET.  
Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, and plead GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Stipulation by parties to complaint as a factual basis to sustain the plea.  Defendant further advised that if he/she is not a US citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found the defendant guilty. Judgment of conviction entered.  
*
Court found the state has satisfied victims' rights law.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  The Court ordered the Defendant to serve 10 months in the House of Correction, straight time, no huber, no good time, consecutive to any other sentence with credit for 34 days time served. Court ordered defendant to pay all applicable court costs and surcharges by 7/08/16.  Court ordered DNA sample and pay the DNA surcharge.  Any amount remaining due and owing is subject to civil judgment and/or tax intercept or other means.  Court advised the defendant that due to this domestic abuse conviction he may never possess firearms or ammuntion.  Notice of Right to Seek Post Conviction Relief received and filed.

Attorney Alexis B Stewart in court, defendant Kendall Ramone Travis not in court, in custody.  Sarra Mae Kiaie appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Deputy Court Clerk: rmm.  
Status Conference held.  Case is adjourned to Branch 40.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for July 8, 2015 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Kendall Ramone Travis in court with attorney Alexis B Stewart.  Kristin Schrank appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Micha Schwab, under the student practice rule, appeared with A.D.A. for the State of Wisconsin.
Deputy Court Clerk: rmm.
Status conference held.  Court will reserve state's motion for joinder.  Case is adjourned to Branch 40.  Court advised defendant that the no contact order remains in effect.  Status conference scheduled for June 16, 2015 at 08:30 am.
No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.

Signed and filed, No Contact Order.  
Defendant to have no contact with: Mercedes H.
Court advised defendant that failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping.

Defendant Kendall Ramone Travis in court with attorney Bernard S. Stein.  Defendant Kendall Ramone Travis in custody.  
Zachary A Wittchow appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  

Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Dallet, Branch 40.  
Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause.  
Defendant advised of right to counsel and complaint given to defendant's attorney.  Defendant plead not guilty.  
DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND QUALIFIES FOR PUBLIC DEFENDER REPRESENTATION.  Status conference scheduled for June 8, 2015 at 08:30 am.
